# Local-only env — loaded by `wrangler dev`, NEVER deployed (production has no .dev.vars file), and it
# overrides any `vars` of the same name in local dev. Standard `ENVIRONMENT` marker: in production the
# deployed Worker has no .dev.vars, so `env.ENVIRONMENT` is undefined and the DO hibernates/evicts
# normally. Locally it is "development", which flips on a dev-only keepalive in the BoardChannel DO to
# dodge a documented `wrangler dev` workerd segfault on Apple Silicon (cloudflare/workers-sdk#4995,
# cloudflare/workerd#1422) — a local-runtime bug, not an app issue.
ENVIRONMENT=development
